Sympetrum striolatum is a species of dragonfly. 
It is part of the Libellulidae family. 
In appearance, the 'Sympetrum striolatum' has a reddish-brown body with yellow stripes on its sides. 
It has transparent wings with black veins. 
The male's abdomen is slightly shorter and thicker than the female's. 
'Sympetrum striolatum' can be found in grasslands, heathlands, and wetlands across Europe and Asia. 
They are often active during warm, sunny days, feeding on smaller insects.
